import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['delay'] = pd.to_datetime(data['delay'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce').dt.hour
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.hist(data['delay'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    ax.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'Median: {data["delay"].median():.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of delay in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data['distance'], data['time'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Distance')
    ax.set_ylabel('Time')
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between distance and time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance_range'] = pd.cut(data['distance'], bins=[0, 500, 1000, 1500, 2000, 2500, 3000])
    delay_by_distance = data.groupby('distance_range')['delay'].mean()
    ax = delay_by_distance.plot(kind='bar', color='blue', alpha=0.7)
    ax.set_xlabel('Distance Range')
    ax.set_ylabel('Average Delay')
    ax.axhline(y=delay_by_distance.max(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Max: {delay_by_distance.max():.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average delay for each distance range?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance_range'] = pd.cut(data['distance'], bins=[0, 500, 1000, 1500, 2000, 2500, 3000])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.boxplot([data[data['distance_range'] == i]['time'] for i in data['distance_range'].unique()], 
               labels=[str(i) for i in data['distance_range'].unique()])
    ax.set_xlabel('Distance Range')
    ax.set_ylabel('Time')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of time taken for each distance range?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
